I am a postdoctoral fellow at Dalla Lana school of public health, University of Toronto. My research interests straddle environmental health, migration studies, urban and regional planning. I'm an interdisciplinary researcher with expertise in spatial analysis and quantitative methods. My research goal is to build up the power of interdisciplinary study across public health, geography, and implementation science in advancing the knowledge and promoting the development of healthy city.

## Education

The Chinese University of Hong Kong, HKSAR, China \| PhD in Population Geography \| Aug 2017 - July 2021

Chinese Academy of Sciences, Institute of Geographic Sciences and Natural Resources Research, Beijing, China \| MSc in Human Geography \| Sept 2013 - June 2016

Shandong University of Science and Technology, Qingdao, China \| BA in Urban and Rural Planning \| Sept 2008 - June 2012

## Employment

Postdoctoral Fellow \| University of Toronto, Dalla Lana School of Public Health \| Nov 2022 - present

Postdoctoral Fellow \| The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Department of Geography and Resource Management \| June 2022 - Oct 2022

Research Associate \| The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Department of Geography and Resource Management \| Aug 2021 - June 2022

Assistant Researcher \| The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Shenzhen Research Institute \| 2022

Visiting Scholar \| Brown University, Spatial Structures in the Social Science \| Oct 2019 - March 2020
